headline: Several femicides mark the end of 2025 in France
description: A man was taken in for questioning on January 1 after police discovered his partner's body in their yard in Nantes. In Lille, two femicide cases cast a shadow over the year-end holidays, reflecting a rise in the number of women killed by their partners or ex-partners.

headline: At the Louvre, tension builds over creation of new 'Mona Lisa' gallery
description: The Louvre-Nouvelle Renaissance architecture competition aims to create a room for Leonardo da Vinci's iconic painting and a new entrance for the Paris museum, which has seen a surge in visitors. Five teams have been shortlisted, none of which are French.

headline: They cook organic, distrust science and oppose vaccines: America's 'crunchy moms' shift toward Trump
description: In the 1960s, the 'crunchy mom' was typically an American hippie trying to stay connected to nature. Today, she claims total freedom over health decisions, sometimes flirting with conspiracy theories.

headline: Bulgaria joins the euro divided, in political crisis and without a budget
description: The Balkan country adopted the European single currency on January 1, but the population remains unenthusiastic. The country only has a caretaker government and corruption is endemic.

headline: In Brazil, love vibrates at the heart of society
description: Traditions around love have long spilled beyond the realm of intimacy to shape the social, political and even collective identity of the country, writes Le Monde's correspondent Bruno Meyerfeld in his final dispatch.
